  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Mind-body practices, such as yoga, ta'i chi, mindfulness and biofeedback, commonly use slow
      breathing techniques to induce physiological and mental relaxation. Medical research suggests
      that slow breathing techniques induce physiological relaxation. This 6 week study will
      compare the effects of different types of breathing. The hypothesis is that different
      breathing techniques produce different physiological and mental changes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
